        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 4:33PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 433 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aberdeen, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sipsey Fork, New Hamilton, Becker, Quincy, Aberdeen, Splunge, Wise
Gap, Athens, Amory, Hatley, East Aberdeen, Greenwood Springs,
Gattman, and Parham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
